#*: Very frequently, however, to shorten the distance to the upper nurseries, where they<sup>[the ants]</sup> have to take the eggs, they project an arch of about ten inches in length, and half an inch in breadth, '''groved''' or worked into steps, on its upper surface, to allow of a more easy passage.
#* '''1841''', {{w|New York State Assembly}}, ''Documents of the Assembly of the State of New York'', Volume 2, [https://books.google.com.au/books?id=xVYbAQAAIAAJ&pg=PP28&dq=%22groved%22%7C%22groving%22&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22groved%22%7C%22groving%22&f=false page 14],
